provenance.note:
Sent by Blake to Ozias Humphry in 1809; 
                    acquired by Alexander C. Weston by 1876; 
                    acquired by Mrs. Anderdon Weston, probably by inheritance; 
                    sold with Blake's letter by a "noted Philadelphia Collector," likely Col. Henry D. Hughes, at American Art Association, April 1923, lot 128;
                    acquired by the Huntington Library from an unknown source, April 1926.
